# Security headers for Cloudflare Pages
# These apply when SKIP_STATIC=true on Render (Pages serves the SPA)
#
# CSP notes (2026-05-08, Phase 6 — script-src fully hardened, style-src
# kept permissive due to motion/react runtime <style> injection):
#   * script-src     — `'unsafe-eval'` and `'unsafe-inline'` BOTH dropped.
#                      Production bundle has no eval/new Function. The one
#                      inline boot script moved to /boot-debug.js. Cloudflare
#                      Insights auto-injects a tiny inline bootstrap that
#                      then loads the external static.cloudflareinsights.com
#                      script — the inline bit is allowlisted by SHA-256
#                      hash so it passes CSP without `unsafe-inline`.
#                      Hash history (Cloudflare rotates this periodically
#                      and currently serves more than one variant — keep
#                      every active hash in the allowlist):
#                        2026-05-08:  cRrVW07TNPw6CwTVu0Nako6M1nwd0redd0jH+9Pue/U=
#                        2026-05-14a: Kg6BgNpWYAx3ZohK5fDHOod813SSB3htrlMqC/RegYE=
#                        2026-05-14b: wpdwqdJ/DWld5If3gFm26J7wuG+DgBvahjrDDEa9y70=
#                        2026-05-14c: 7FyXG6wVUD6Ve0TF3lYseOSd0R2bWQqh6aJfKrbB1Io=
#                        2026-05-16:  u2tz3AO+oBAKJtNgGuvmNfXpmnbjA8TTRNPNq+91mw4=
#                      When the console reports a violation with a new
#                      hash, ADD it (don't replace) — Cloudflare may keep
#                      rotating between multiple bootstraps for the same
#                      page.
#                      *** This is the high-value XSS-defence win. ***
#   * style-src-elem — `'unsafe-inline'` KEPT. motion/react injects
#                      <style>...</style> blocks at runtime for animation
#                      keyframes (spring/layout/keyframes anims). The content
#                      is dynamic so we can't hash it; nonce-based CSP would
#                      require a Worker template-rewrite. Tracked as deferred
#                      hardening — same risk class as style-src-attr.
#   * style-src-attr — `'unsafe-inline'` KEPT. motion/react writes
#                      transform/opacity to the element's `style` attribute
#                      every frame. CSS-only — cannot escalate to JS.
#   * media-src      — `https://*.r2.dev` ADDED. Production VITE_CLOUDFLARE_URL
#                      points at the R2 public bucket alias
#                      (https://pub-<hash>.r2.dev), which is the same origin
#                      served via the audio.vocaband.com custom domain.
#                      Without it Howler in HTML5 mode (see #676) couldn't
#                      load any word MP3 — every word fell back to browser
#                      TTS and the console screamed CSP violations.
#                      Also added to connect-src for the same reason — some
#                      callers (FreeResourcesView audio-pack download
#                      preview) fetch the MP3 directly.
#
# 2026-05-16, R5 — Sentry observability:
#   * connect-src     — `https://o4511016408514560.ingest.de.sentry.io`
#                       ADDED.  This is the ingest host derived from the
#                       DSN in src/core/sentry.ts.  Without it the browser
#                       SILENTLY blocks every error event the SDK tries to
#                       POST (CSP violations don't surface as user-visible
#                       failures), which is how the previous Sentry setup
#                       was effectively invisible in production.  Changing
#                       the DSN project requires updating this host AND the
#                       FALLBACK_DSN in sentry.ts at the same time.
#   * script-src-elem — `https://browser.sentry-cdn.com` ADDED.  The replay
#                       integration is lazy-loaded from the Sentry CDN
#                       (Sentry.lazyLoadIntegration('replayIntegration'))
#                       so the ~50 KB gzipped replay code doesn't bloat the
#                       entry chunk on weak school Wi-Fi.  The CDN script
#                       is signed with subresource integrity by the SDK
#                       itself; no SHA-256 allowlist needed here.

/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-XSS-Protection: 0
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(self), microphone=(self), geolocation=(), payment=(), usb=(), magnetometer=(), gyroscope=(), accelerometer=(), interest-cohort=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin-allow-popups
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-site
  X-Permitted-Cross-Domain-Policies: none
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'sha256-Kg6BgNpWYAx3ZohK5fDHOod813SSB3htrlMqC/RegYE=' 'sha256-wpdwqdJ/DWld5If3gFm26J7wuG+DgBvahjrDDEa9y70=' 'sha256-7FyXG6wVUD6Ve0TF3lYseOSd0R2bWQqh6aJfKrbB1Io=' 'sha256-u2tz3AO+oBAKJtNgGuvmNfXpmnbjA8TTRNPNq+91mw4=' https://static.cloudflareinsights.com https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://browser.sentry-cdn.com; script-src-elem 'self' 'sha256-Kg6BgNpWYAx3ZohK5fDHOod813SSB3htrlMqC/RegYE=' 'sha256-wpdwqdJ/DWld5If3gFm26J7wuG+DgBvahjrDDEa9y70=' 'sha256-7FyXG6wVUD6Ve0TF3lYseOSd0R2bWQqh6aJfKrbB1Io=' 'sha256-u2tz3AO+oBAKJtNgGuvmNfXpmnbjA8TTRNPNq+91mw4=' https://static.cloudflareinsights.com https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://browser.sentry-cdn.com; style-src-elem 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; style-src-attr 'unsafe-inline'; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' data: blob: https:; connect-src 'self' https://auth.vocaband.com wss://auth.vocaband.com https://api.vocaband.com wss://api.vocaband.com https://vocaband.fly.dev wss://vocaband.fly.dev https://*.supabase.co wss://*.supabase.co https://static.cloudflareinsights.com https://cloudflareinsights.com https://vocaband.com wss://vocaband.com https://audio.vocaband.com https://*.r2.dev https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://fonts.googleapis.com https://fonts.gstatic.com https://o4511016408514560.ingest.de.sentry.io; media-src 'self' https://auth.vocaband.com https://*.supabase.co https://*.cloudflare.com https://audio.vocaband.com https://*.r2.dev; worker-src 'self' blob:; frame-src https://accounts.google.com https://challenges.cloudflare.com; frame-ancestors 'none'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self' https://accounts.google.com

# Cache static assets aggressively (hashed filenames)
/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

# Don't cache HTML (SPA routing)
/index.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache

# Don't cache service worker
/sw.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate

# PDFs are regenerated by scripts/teacher-pdfs/build.mjs and
# scripts/presentation-pdf/build.mjs — not content-hashed, so we can't
# cache them forever, but a short cache + revalidate balances speed
# with the ability to ship a typo fix without making teachers wait.
# Explicit Content-Type defends against any future Worker layer that
# might sniff the body and mislabel a non-rendered response.
/Vocaband-Presentation-HE.pdf
  Content-Type: application/pdf
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate
/Vocaband-Presentation-AR.pdf
  Content-Type: application/pdf
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate
/docs/*.pdf
  Content-Type: application/pdf
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate
